foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: The difference between the number of requests pending at the end of the FY2011 and the number pending at the start of FY 2012 is attributed to the failure to enter 62 requests into the FOIA Tracking System (FTS) timely. The FTS database was updated with the missing requests in FY 2012.

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: The numbers of pending appeals at the beginning of FY 2012 is correct. The difference between the numbers of appeals pending at the end of FY 2011 and the start of FY 2012 is attributed to a glitch in the FOIA Tracking System.

foia:OldestPendingRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: The oldest request for OLC/HDQ is 69 days. Although the request was received 9-14-2012, it was tolled for five days.

foia:PersonnelAndCostSection.foia:FootnoteText: EEOC expended $320 preparing a responsive brief to a FOIA law suit filed against the Los Angeles District Office.
